---
import ToolLayout from '../components/ToolLayout.astro';
import AffiliateLink from '../components/AffiliateLink.astro';

const title = 'About — Compound Interest Calculator';
const description = 'Learn more about Compound Interest Calculator, a free resource for understanding and projecting compound interest, investing, and savings growth.';

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'AboutPage',
  name: title,
  description,
  url: Astro.url.toString(),
};
---

<ToolLayout title={title} description={description} jsonLd={jsonLd}>
  <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-none">
    <p>
      <strong>Compound Interest Calculator</strong> is a free online resource built to help people understand how compound interest works and how it can grow savings and investments over time. Our calculators, guides, and comparison tools are designed to be fast, accurate, and easy to use on any device.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-4 dark:text-slate-100">Our mission</h2>
    <p>
      We believe financial clarity should be free and accessible. By making compound interest visual and interactive, we hope to help more people start investing earlier, save more consistently, and set realistic long-term goals.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-4 dark:text-slate-100">How the calculators work</h2>
    <p>
      All calculations run directly in your web browser. Enter your starting balance, monthly contribution, expected annual return, time horizon, and compounding frequency, and the calculator instantly projects your total balance, contributions, and interest earned. No account is required, and we do not store your inputs.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-4 dark:text-slate-100">Accuracy and methodology</h2>
    <p>
      Our compound interest formula follows the standard financial model: <code>A = P(1 + r/n)^(nt) + contributions</code>. We use monthly compounding logic for contributions and display results as projections, not guarantees. Market returns fluctuate, so we encourage users to run multiple scenarios with conservative, moderate, and optimistic assumptions.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-4 dark:text-slate-100">Important disclaimer</h2>
    <p>
      This website is for educational purposes only and does not provide personalized financial, investment, tax, or legal advice. Always consult a qualified financial professional before making major financial decisions.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-4 dark:text-slate-100">Trusted financial partners</h2>
    <p>
      We only link to financial services we believe are reputable and relevant to our readers. Popular options for low-cost investing and savings include
      <AffiliateLink href="https://investor.vanguard.com/" label="Vanguard" />,
      <AffiliateLink href="https://www.fidelity.com/" label="Fidelity" />,
      <AffiliateLink href="https://www.schwab.com/" label="Charles Schwab" />,
      <AffiliateLink href="https://www.betterment.com/" label="Betterment" />,
      <AffiliateLink href="https://www.wealthfront.com/" label="Wealthfront" />,
      <AffiliateLink href="https://www.marcus.com/" label="Marcus by Goldman Sachs" />, and
      <AffiliateLink href="https://www.ally.com/" label="Ally Bank" />.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-4 dark:text-slate-100">Affiliate disclosure</h2>
    <p>
      Some links on this site are affiliate links. We may earn a commission if you click through and open an account or make a purchase, at no additional cost to you. Affiliate income helps support the ongoing development of the site.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-4 dark:text-slate-100">Get in touch</h2>
    <p>
      Have feedback or a suggestion? Visit our <a href="/contact/">contact page</a> to send us a message. We read every message and use feedback to improve the calculators and guides.
    </p>
  </div>
</ToolLayout>
